===Etymology===
From {{etyl|goh|de}} {{term|bi|bī|lang=goh}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|de}} {{recons|bi|lang=gem-pro}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|De-bei.ogg|audio}}

===Preposition===
{{head|de|preposition|+ dative}}

# {{context|with something that has a location|lang=de}} [[by]] (some place or someone); [[near]]; [[with]]; [[on]]
#: ''Ich habe es nicht '''bei''' mir.'' — “I do not have it on me.”
# {{context|with something that has a definite time|lang=de}} [[by]] (some time); by the beginning of (some event); [[at]]; [[on]]; [[upon]]
#: '''''bei''' Abfahrt des Zuges'' — “upon departure of the train”
# {{context|with something that has a duration|lang=de}} [[during]]; [[while]]; [[over]]
#: '''''bei''' der Arbeit'' — “during work”
#: '''''bei''' einem Glase Wein'' — “over a glass of wine”
# {{context|with a person, business name, or job title|lang=de}} at the home, business, or station usually occupied by (someone)
# {{context|with an organization|lang=de}} [[in]]; [[for]]
#: '''''bei''' der Firma arbeiten'' — “to work for the firm”
# {{context|with something that may or may not occur|lang=de}} [[if]] there is (something)
#: '''''bei''' Schnee'' — “if there is snow”
# {{context|in a postal address|lang=de}} [[care of]]

====Usage notes====
When {{term|bei}} is followed by the definite article {{term|dem||the}}, the two words contract to {{term|beim}}.

